//! # LovecaSim Bytecode Interpreter
//!
//! This module implements the core logic for executing card abilities. 
//! It processes a custom bytecode format generated by the compiler.
//!
//! ## Core Components:
//! - `resolve_bytecode`: The main execution loop. It iterates through instructions, 
//!   manages an execution stack for nested calls (e.g., `O_TRIGGER_REMOTE`), 
//!   and handles state transitions.
//! - `suspend_interaction`: Used when an opcode requires user input (e.g., `O_COLOR_SELECT`).
//!   It preserves the current execution context and enters `Phase::Response`.
//! - `handle_member_leaves_stage`: Centralized logic for clearing a member from the stage, 
//!   triggering `OnLeaves` effects, and preserving energy.
//!
//! ## Execution Model:
//! The interpreter is designed to be re-entrant. If an effect requires a choice, 
//! it "suspends" by saving the program counter and stack, returning control to the 
//! game loop. Once the choice is processed, execution resumes from the saved point.

